text: Anton Ryen (15 December 1894 - 17 February 1968) was a Norwegian politician for the Farmers' Party. He was born in Vågå. He was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from Oppland in 1945, and was re-elected on two occasions. ==References== * Category:1894 births Category:1968 deaths Category:Members of the Storting Category:Centre Party (Norway) politicians Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
